MSR-QUERY-PROPS.COMMENT: queries a chapter from a FS particle (generated by ASCET)

P.L-1: In this class, the target deceleration from ADAS signals is defined and limited
The first priority is customer specific deceleration request and second is standard deceleration request
If a trailer is connected, the deceleration must be limited since high decelerations could destabilize the trailer.
If the BA is activated and the vehicle speed is more than or equal to 100kph, the deceleration must be limited at 0.8G.
If the IB Partial is activated, the deceleration must be limited at 0.4G.
